sect2:
Booting with TFTP
&boot-installer-intro-net.xml;
On machines with OpenBoot, simply enter the boot monitor on the machine which is being installed (see ). Use the command boot net to boot from a TFTP and RARP server, or try boot net:bootp or boot net:dhcp to boot from a TFTP and BOOTP or DHCP server.

Booting from a CD-ROM
&boot-installer-intro-cd.xml;
Most OpenBoot versions support the boot cdrom command which is simply an alias to boot from the SCSI device on ID 6 (or the secondary master for IDE based systems).
